  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label>Grants Smartgun:</label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="system.grantsSmartgun" {{checked system.grantsSmartgun}}
           title="Makes the attached weapon a smartweapon (Smartgun System, SR2E p.241). The −2/−1 TN comes from the shooter's smartlink or smart goggles." />
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label>Permanent Once Installed:</label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="system.permanentAccessory" {{checked system.permanentAccessory}}
           title="Cannot be removed after installation (gas-vent systems, under-barrel grenade launchers, internal smartgun — SR2E p.240–241)." />
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label>Needs Deployment:</label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="system.requiresDeployment" {{checked system.requiresDeployment}}
           title="Recoil comp only counts when set up — bipod/tripod braced in a sitting or lying position (SR2E p.240–241)." />
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label>Gyro Rating:</label>
    <input type="number" name="system.gyroRating" value="{{system.gyroRating}}" min="0"
           title="Gyro mount rating: reduces recoil + attacker movement modifiers by up to this many points (SR2E p.90). Standard 5, Deluxe 6." />
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label>Scope Range Shift:</label>
    <input type="number" name="system.rangeShift" value="{{system.rangeShift}}" min="0"
           title="Imaging scope magnification: shifts the range bracket left by this many levels, short is the floor (SR2E p.88)." />
  </div>
  {{/if}}
  {{#unless system.weaponAccessory}}
  <div class="form-group">
    <label>Smart Goggles:</label>
    <input type="checkbox" name="system.smartGoggles" {{checked system.smartGoggles}}
           title="Worn receptor: −1 TN when firing a smartweapon while equipped (SR2E p.90, p.241)." />
  </div>
  {{/unless}}
  {{#ifEquals system.category "cyberdeck"}}
  <hr/>
  <p class="hint">Cyberdeck (SR2 p.140). Activate it on the Gear tab (⚡) to drive the Matrix tab — only one deck is active at a time. Persona programs (Bod/Evasion/Masking/Sensor) are separate program items capped by MPCP.</p>
